{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/Neovim/13-sneak/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"0f4cb81c-4d87-550b-bc30-0f570d4b0cbc","html":"<h2>Install</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      Plug 'justinmk/vim-sneak'\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Create config file</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      touch ~/.config/nvim/plug-config/sneak.vim\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Make sure to source this file in <code class=\"language-text\">init.vim</code></p>\n<h2>Sneak</h2>\n<p>Sneak is a motion plugin for vim that remaps the <code class=\"language-text\">s</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">S</code> keys</p>\n<p>The authors rationale for remapping these keys is this: cl is equivalent to s, and cc is equivalent to S.</p>\n<h3>Configure Sneak</h3>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      let g:sneak#label = 1\n\n\" case insensitive sneak\nlet g:sneak#use_ic_scs = 1\n\n\" immediately move to the next instance of search, if you move the cursor sneak is back to default behavior\nlet g:sneak#s_next = 1\n\n\" remap so I can use , and ; with f and t\nmap gS <Plug>Sneak_,\nmap gs <Plug>Sneak_;\n\n\" Change the colors\nhighlight Sneak guifg=black guibg=#00C7DF ctermfg=black ctermbg=cyan\nhighlight SneakScope guifg=red guibg=yellow ctermfg=red ctermbg=yellow\n\n\" Cool prompts\n\" let g:sneak#prompt = 'ðŸ•µ'\n\" let g:sneak#prompt = 'ðŸ”Ž'\n\n\" I like quickscope better for this since it keeps me in the scope of a single line\n\" map f <Plug>Sneak_f\n\" map F <Plug>Sneak_F\n\" map t <Plug>Sneak_t\n\" map T <Plug>Sneak_T\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h3>Sneak Commands</h3>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      s{char}{char}\nS{char}{char}\n\nf{char}\nF{char}\n\n\nt{char}\nT{char}\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Link to Sneak repo</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/justinmk/vim-sneak\">Sneak</a></p>","excerpt":"Install Create config file Make sure to source this file in  Sneak Sneak is a motion plugin for vim that remaps the  and  keys The authorsâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Sneak","tags":["neovim"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/a8734/neovim.png"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":3.456140350877193,"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png","srcSet":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/06f82/neovim.png 197w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/da7d7/neovim.png 393w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png 786w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/31987/neovim.png 1000w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Neovim/13-sneak/","prev":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Linux/02-After-Install/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"What to do after installing Arch Linux","tags":["archlinux"]}}},"next":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Neovim/14-quickscope/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Quickscope","tags":["neovim"]}}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}